==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suttee
<hw>Sut*tee"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Skr.
<ets>sat⟦imac⟧</ets> a faithful wife, fem. of <ets>sant</ets> existing,
real, true, good, p. pr. of <ets>as</ets> to be. Cf.
<er>Sooth</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A Hindoo widow who immolates
herself, or is immolated, on the funeral pile of her husband; -- so
called because this act of self-immolation is regarded as envincing
excellence of wifely character.</def> <mark>[India]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of burning a widow on the funeral pile of
her husband.</def> <mark>[India]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The practice, though abolished in British India law in
1829, is not wholly prevented.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sutteeism</ent>⟦br⟧
